commit.message:
Downgrade check-manifest

The new check-manifest v0.41 does not work together with poetry.

Remove references to graphql-core-next

GraphQL-core-next has been replaced by GraphQL-core v3.
Also require v3 final instead of v3 alpha.
Prepare 3.0.0 release
Deploy from master branch
Merge the 'next' branch to master
Revert to where we started the 'next' branch

Fix packages in pyproject.toml

Currently we don't have docs, but we have tests.
Support Python 3.8 and update dependencies
Fix deployment credentials
Prepare patch release that supports Python 3.8
Add tests to source distribution

Fix code coverage in Travis

The src path is already specified in .coveragerc
Update poetry and fix pyproject.toml
Reformat everything with black
Update dependencies and version number
add skip_exisiting option so builds pass after deployment
add encrypted deploy password with --org option
add username to travis deploy config
remove user and password in travis config and adding to travis env
encrypt password without the com option
update deploy password
Use an encrypted env variable for the PyPI passwd
Require version 3 of graphql-core

Travis deploy v3 (#25)

* reencrypt pypi deployment password
* add deploy config
Add PyPI deploy credentials (#22)

Create v2 that is compatible with Core v2 (#21)

* Create v2 that is compatible with Core v2

* Bump version to 2.0
* Support GraphQL-core >= 2.0, < 3
  (use the newer signature for resolvers)
* Drop support for Python 3.3
* Drop redundant README.rst
* Clean-up and PEP-8
* Use .flake8 instead of setup.cfg
* Use "setup.py test" for testing, as explained in README
* Make this run with pytest 4. This will be changed in v3,
  where we use pytest 5 and run it directly.
* Only check relevant files with flake8
* Minor fixes in the README
